   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Share Action</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ShareAction (previously known as Fair Pensions) is a UK-registered charity that promotes Responsible Investment and gives savers a voice in the investment system. It builds capacity among individuals, charities, faith groups, unions and other civil society organisations to engage with powerful investors, and use their own shares in companies, to bring about change. ShareAction is recognised as a leading NGO that monitors and engages with the investment industry. In 2014, it secured funding to expand its work into Europe, and to explore the possibility of projects in the United States.

ShareAction runs campaigns on issues the investment industry has the power to influence, like paying the Living Wage, reforming company tax practice and protecting the environment. It trains and assists individuals to attend company AGMs and hold directors to account on these issues. It carries out research to make the investment practices of the largest fund managers and pension funds more transparent and accountable.

Oxfam, Christian Aid, Greenpeace, WWF,and Unite are some of the members of ShareAction.</narrative>
